          "feedback": "Exactly. DNS translates the hostname into an address the browser can use to reach a server.",
          "isCorrect": true,
          "text": "Finding an IP address for the hostname"
        },
        {
          "feedback": "Close, but TLS handles encryption after a network connection can be made.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "Encrypting the page content"
        },
